<chapter id="introduction">
<title>Introduction</title>

<para>&kile; is a LaTeX source editor, TeX shell and GnuPlot
frontend. It is not a <acronym>WYSIWYG</acronym> (what you see is what
you get) interface for LaTeX; instead, its aim is to simplify the
edition of LaTeX source code and the use of the LaTeX-related programs
for users who want to retain control over their LaTeX documents.</para>
</chapter>

<chapter id="using-kile">
<title>Using &kile;</title>

<sect1 id="kile-features">
<title>&kile; Features</title>

<para>In addition to the usual commands of an editor, &kile; provides
other commands to assist you in editing your source files.</para>

<sect2 id="encoding">
<title>Non-English documents and special characters</title>

<para>If you want to edit or create documents that contain non-standard letters (such as accented letters), you will have to set
the encoding for the file. This can be done by selecting the appropriate encoding (iso 8859-2 for most European
countries for example) in the drop-down menu at the lower left corner of the file selector window.
</para>
