</sect2>
 
<sect2 id="quick-build">
<title>The <guimenuitem>Quick Build</guimenuitem> Command</title>

<para>With this command, the compilation and display of the document
are automatically launched, unless a LaTeX error is detected in the
log file.  Only errors will stop the process, warnings are
ignored.</para>

</sect2>

<sect2 id="multiple-file-documents">
<title>About Documents Separated in Several Files</title>

<para>After having defined your <quote>Master</quote> document, with
the corresponding command in the <guimenu>Options</guimenu> menu, all
the commands of the <guimenu>Tools</guimenu> menu will apply only to
this document even when you are working on the <quote>children</quote>
documents.  You can even close the Master document.</para>

