<sect2 id="watch-file">
<title>Use of the <quote>Watch File</quote> mode</title>

<para>Example of use with &kdvi;</para>

<procedure>
<step><para>Launch the <guimenuitem>Quick Build</guimenuitem>
command.</para></step>
<step><para>Leave &kdvi; open and select the <guimenuitem>Watch
File</guimenuitem> mode for this program.</para></step>
<step><para>Select the <guimenuitem>Watch File</guimenuitem> in the
<guimenu>Tools</guimenu> menu in &kile;.</para></step>
<step><para>Each time you launch the <guimenuitem>Quick
Build</guimenuitem>, the <quote>dvi</quote> document will be
automatically updated, without &kdvi; being started again.</para></step>
</procedure>

<para>This mode also works with &kghostview;, but will not work with
the embedded viewers.</para>

</sect2>

<sect2 id="kdvi-forward-search">
<title>Use of the &kdvi; <guimenuitem>Forward Search</guimenuitem>
Command</title>

<para>With this command, &kdvi; displays the &DVI; document directly
in the place corresponding to the position of the cursor in &kile;.
This command is not available if a Master document is defined in
&kile;.  You must also iset the following command into the preamble of
your document:</para>

<screen><userinput>\usepackage[active]{srcltx }</userinput></screen>

<para>Finally, you must copy the <filename>srcltx.sty</filename> and
<filename>srctex.sty</filename> files (provided with &kdvi;) into the
same directory as your document.</para>

</sect2>

<sect2 id="kdvi-inverse-search">
<title>Use of the &kdvi; <guimenuitem>Inverse Search</guimenuitem>
with &kile;</title>

<para>With this feature of &kdvi;, a middle mouse click in the &DVI;
document will have &kile; open the corresponding tex document and
attempt to go to the corresponding line. </para>

<para>For this to work, the tex document must be already compiled, and
the <link linkend="kdvi-forward-search">&kdvi; Forward Search</link>
must be working.</para>

<para>To select &kile; as the default editor in &kdvi; enter the
command <userinput><command>kile</command> <parameter>%f</parameter>
<option>--line</option> <parameter>%</parameter></userinput> in the
&kdvi; dialog reached through
<menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</guimenu><guisubmenu>DVI
Options</guisubmenu><guimenuitem>DVI
Specials</guimenuitem></menuchoice>

<screenshot>
